field.name: content
field.value:
Edit MS Office document offline

The user is able to edit MS Office document, uploaded in the system directly in the MS application, in which the document has been created.

Only users with the respective role have permissions to edit a document offline (manager, collaborator and contributor).

Example:

  • There is action Edit Offline for the documents created in MS Office application (MS Word, MS Excel, MS PowerPoint). When the action is selected:

 

  • The content of the document is successfully downloaded.
    • When an user opens the document for edit, the document is locked automatically (1), and other users could not edit it (only the admin and the managers of the object could unlock it).
  • The browser pop-up screen is opened (2), where the user should select if to Open (3) or Save the file.
    •  If the user selects OK (4)
  • The document is downloaded and saved in the OS file system.
  • The user could enable editing the document, edit and save it and then upload it as a new version of the original document.
